com.github.dm.rf.android.iterator

Interface LongSparseIterable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ElementSparseIterable<Long>, Iterable<Long>, SparseIterable<Long>

    public interface LongSparseIterable
extends ElementSparseIterable<Long>
    This interface extends the ElementSparseIterable one by adding specific methods handling long elements.

    Created by davide-maestroni on 3/10/14.

      • fill

        LongSparseIterable fill(long[] array)
        Fills the specified array with the elements returned by this iterable, in the iteration order, starting from the index 0 of the array.

        Note that, in case the array is not big enough to contain all the elements, an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        array - the array to fill.
        Returns:
        this iterable.

      • fill

        LongSparseIterable fill(long[] array,
                      int offset)
        Fills the specified array with the elements returned by this iterable, in the iteration order, starting from the specified offset inside the array.

        Note that, in case the array is not big enough to contain all the elements, an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown.

        Parameters:
